title: 381. Long-Term Thinking in a Start-Up Town
description: Recorded live in San Francisco. Guests include the keeper of a 10,000-year clock, the co-founder of Lyft, a pioneer in male birth control, a specialist in water security, and a psychology professor who is also a puppy. With co-host Angela Duckworth, fact-checker Mike Maughan, and the Freakonomics Radio Orchestra.
author: editor@freakonomics.com (Freakonomics Radio + Stitcher)
